import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='longitude', y='latitude', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='speed', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['speed'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['speed'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['speed'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['speed'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of speed?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Speed')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.countplot(x="dirCat", data=data, palette="Set3")
    ax.set(xlabel='Wind Direction Category', ylabel='Count')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of dirCat?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['dirCat'] = pd.Categorical(data['dir'])
    data['dirCat'] = data['dirCat'].cat.codes
    ax = sns.scatterplot(x='dirCat', y='speed', data=data)
    ax.set(xlabel='Wind Direction', ylabel='Wind Speed')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between dir and speed?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['dirCat'] = pd.Categorical(data['dir'])
    dir_counts = data['dirCat'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(dir_counts, labels=dir_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of dir?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
